a, Small molecule kinase inhibitor libraries (including number of compounds in each library) used for Kinobeads profiling. b, Venn diagram of the number of kinases in the human genome, enriched by Kinobeads from mixed lysates and targeted by at least one inhibitor. Several metabolic kinases as well as nucleotide, FAD and heme binding proteins were also identified as kinase inhibitor binders. c, Windmill plot grouping compounds by library and the number of targets by Kinobeads. Compounds with potency below 100 nM are marked in gray. d, Number of compounds targeting a specific kinase with an affinity below 1 µM. Kinases are grouped by subfamilies and sorted alphabetically within each group.

