Further adjustments to the published protocol included the reduction of the amount of protein extract per experiment to 2.5 mg of protein and to 17 µl of settled Kinobeads to enable higher throughput. Six DMSO vehicle controls were included in random order on every 96-well plate to allow data normalization within and across plates. We developed a data analysis pipeline including protein identification and quantification by MaxQuant/Andromeda18, calculation of half-maximum inhibitory concentration (IC50) and \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
